§9More Information at the IRCC Website(Not finished)

At the moment only I(Relivof) am working on this modpack,
but if you feel there is something that belongs or a bug that isn't being fixed, 
just join me, help me make your favourite modpack, that you's made.
The world Generation is powered by RTG or Realistic Terrain Generator, which is used by some of the best modpacks(GTNH).

Greg or Not? 

That is the question,

Although the story/modpack is based around GregTech CEu, most mods may not be "Gregged", though we might do it in the future.

Most of the mods/recipes will be as realistic as we can.
If it is'nt realistic enough, you can fix it. As stated earlier.

The ore's generate in veins from GregTech, you can use a Electric Prospector to easily find veins,

As a welcome gift, we give you this brand new Electric Prospector.

As you progress you might notice the Sync mod, a simple explaination, it is a transport/bioligy mod where you can "escape" death.

This may be explained in future quest.

This modpack was made from my love of GregTech and love of Stories/Lore,

Most GregTech Modpack's i've played have only had like that humans destroyed the earth with Nukes or some bad story, but Lost in reality is striving to be different.

Taking Some bits from many Shows/Movies/Games.

If anything doesnt line up make sure to put an issue on our github at §ahttps://github.com/Inter-Reality-Control-Committee/Lost-in-reality§f(NOT CLICKABLE)

One of the mods intalled is Hardcore Darkness, which removes the darkest light.

AKA: night's a pain.

As a welcome gift, we give you some torches.
Collect the "best food source" dirt.
Get flint from breaking gravel.

Break trees with your hands,
to get wood.
Make a crafting table with the previous items.
A pickaxe allows you to mine stone.

Make tools with wood and other materials,
they make you complete tasks quicker.
stone
Now you can mine more.
At least it's better than wood.
Get iron from smelting iron ore in a furnace.
Copper and Tin is used to make bronze, which will start the steam age.
Sand and clay is used in the making of coke bricks.

Iron tools are super "Speedy".

You may notice these tools aren't the same as the others, that is because these are GregTech Tools, which add special buffs.

The Mod "First aid" has been added, it is a "overhaul" to normal damage, having damage applied to limbs, not your entire body.

There are items to heal you.

As a gift here is some bandages and morphine.
A form to make bricks, used for coke oven bricks.

JEI(Just enough items) will be necessary.

For example, recipes, I bet you don't know how to make a coke oven brick, and others.
Even multiblocks, if you need help making a multiblock structure like the primitive pump, you can press U or R on the main block and it will have a multiblock tab.

And expecially you will be using certain recipes ALOT, and just a workbench may not be enough, so you can press A on the item and it will be added to the bookmarks.
These tools are useful for making/using gregtech or other mods items/blocks.

Bronze at last, this is one of the basics for the steam age.

Also you unlock the steam age from this.
The base of the coke oven.
Now all you need is to craft the blocks needed.
The terminal can be used in many ways, including helping with machines. And multiblocks, that is why it comes with a battery and a camera.
The Primitave Water Pump pulls water out of nowhere, used to bring water to steam boilers.

Steam boilers are the first machine you'll make.

Insert water, take out steam, simple enough.
Almost to steal.

Are you too tired to make a circuit for the millionth time,

then no worries, let us present the Shop...

Grab your coins and your shop key and walk over to the nearest crafting table, where you can insert some coins and your key in the center, and out pops an item.


DONT LOSE THE KEY, IT IS NOT CRAFTABLE/OBTAINABLE.
This will explain your mission here/who you are.
The start/beginning of your journey to conquer this reality.
Now the first "Tech" Quest line.
